        "created_at": "2025-07-06T14:36:07.112Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Would be great if there was a home-button in the tab-bar to deselect the current chat.<br>\nTo show the screen like when you startup signal. With no chat selected.</p>\n<p>Why?<br>\nBecause if left selected and doing something in another app or taking a break, the messages are marked as read. While I could be actually reading those messages hours later. Seriously, this got me into huge problems with my now ex-girlfriend.  <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/frowning_face.png?v=12\" title=\":frowning_face:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":frowning_face:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n<p>Since then I make sure to select another chat where, read of unread, is not important. But most of the time I would have to scroll way down for that. Canâ€™t that just be a button in the tabbar?</p>\n<p>This is a mockup:<br>\n<div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/e/3/e3f8f07d0d48fd9b5f143037dba0436e3fde8a1d.png\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/e3f8f07d0d48fd9b5f143037dba0436e3fde8a1d\" title=\"deselect-chat\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/e/3/e3f8f07d0d48fd9b5f143037dba0436e3fde8a1d_2_109x500.png\" alt=\"deselect-chat\" data-base62-sha1=\"wwJJDeLvJrHFA7f8UcChmDEZVz7\" width=\"109\" height=\"500\" data-dominant-color=\"E7E6E4\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">deselect-chat</span><span class=\"informations\">161Ã—735 21.2 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>",
